# AI Website Illustration Prompt Guide
*Create smooth, scroll-driven illustrations that captivate and engage*

## Core Visual Style
**Create illustrations that are:**
- **Fluid and organic** - Use flowing lines, smooth curves, and natural movement patterns
- **Minimalist yet impactful** - Clean compositions with purposeful negative space
- **Dimensionally rich** - Subtle 3D elements, layered depth, and floating objects
- **Gradient-heavy** - Smooth color transitions from deep purples to electric blues, sunset oranges to mint greens
- **Geometrically balanced** - Mix organic shapes with clean geometric forms

## Scroll Animation Behaviors
**Parallax Movement:**
- Background elements move slower than foreground (0.3x speed)
- Mid-ground elements at 0.6x speed
- Foreground elements at normal speed (1x)
- Create 5-7 distinct depth layers

**Morphing Transformations:**
- Shapes gradually transform as user scrolls
- Circles become squares, lines become curves
- Color gradients shift through spectrum
- Opacity changes create breathing effects

**Reveal Animations:**
- Elements slide in from edges (left: -100px to 0)
- Fade in with scale (scale: 0.8 to 1, opacity: 0 to 1)
- Rotate into view (rotate: 15deg to 0deg)
- Stagger animations by 150ms delays

## Specific Illustration Elements

**Floating Objects:**
- Abstract geometric shapes (dodecahedrons, toroids, crystals)
- Soft glowing orbs with inner light
- Wireframe structures that build/deconstruct
- Particle systems that flow like digital wind

**3D Model Animations:**
- Product models that rotate smoothly on scroll (Y-axis rotation)
- Architectural models that assemble piece by piece
- Character models with subtle breathing/idle animations
- Abstract sculptures that morph between different forms
- Mechanical objects with working parts (gears, pistons, rotors)
- Organic models that grow/evolve (plants, crystalline structures)

**Background Textures:**
- Subtle noise overlays (10% opacity)
- Gradient meshes that shift color temperature
- Dot matrix patterns that pulse gently
- Flowing wave forms that undulate smoothly

**Interactive Highlights:**
- Elements that respond to cursor proximity
- Gentle scale increases on hover (1.05x)
- Color saturation boosts on interaction
- Soft shadow depth changes

## Technical Animation Specs

**Smooth Performance:**
- Use `transform` properties only (translate3d, scale, rotate)
- Implement `will-change: transform` on moving elements
- Target 60fps with `requestAnimationFrame`
- Use CSS `ease-out` timing (cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94))

**Scroll Triggers:**
- Activate animations when elements are 20% in viewport
- Complete animations when elements are 80% in viewport
- Use intersection observer for performance
- Implement scroll velocity detection for dynamic speeds

**Responsive Behavior:**
- Scale illustration complexity based on device capability
- Reduce particle counts on mobile devices
- Simplify animations for users with `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Maintain aspect ratios across all screen sizes

## Content Integration

**Text Reveal Effects:**
- Words appear as illustration elements move
- Typography follows the same easing curves
- Letter-by-letter reveals with 50ms stagger
- Blur-to-focus transitions (filter: blur(4px) to blur(0))

**Section Transitions:**
- Illustrations morph to match content themes
- Color schemes shift between page sections
- Elements break apart and reform for new contexts
- Smooth crossfades between illustration states

**Call-to-Action Enhancement:**
- Subtle particle effects around buttons
- Pulsing glows that sync with user attention
- Directional arrows that form from scattered dots
- Engagement rings that expand on hover

## Performance Optimization

**Loading Strategy:**
- Preload critical animation frames
- Use CSS animations for simple transforms
- Implement JavaScript only for complex interactions
- Lazy load non-critical illustration elements

**Accessibility Considerations:**
- Provide `prefers-reduced-motion` alternatives
- Ensure illustrations don't interfere with text readability
- Maintain focus indicators that work with animations
- Include alt descriptions for decorative elements

## Implementation Notes

**CSS Custom Properties:**
```css
:root {
  --scroll-progress: 0;
  --mouse-x: 50%;
  --mouse-y: 50%;
  --primary-hue: 220;
  --animation-speed: 1s;
}
```

**JavaScript Integration:**
- Update CSS custom properties based on scroll position
- Use IntersectionObserver for performance
- Implement smooth scroll detection
- Add device capability detection
- Initialize 3D scenes with Three.js or WebGL
- Implement 3D model loading with progress indicators
- Set up camera controls that respond to scroll
- Create 3D lighting systems that follow user interaction

**Fallback Strategy:**
- Static illustrations for unsupported browsers
- Simplified animations for low-end devices
- Graceful degradation for accessibility users
- Progressive enhancement approach

